glosses: to attack a person as a group
for dogs to attack while barking

etymology:
Inherited from Old Anatolian Turkish اوشمك (üşmek), from Proto-Oghuz *ǖš-, ultimately a derivation from Proto-Turkic *üy-.
Cognate with Gagauz üüşmää, Karakhanid اُشْماكْ (ušmʾk /⁠⁠üšmek⁠/), Kyrgyz үйүшүү (üyüşüü), Turkmen üýşmek.
